description: A serious and potentially life-threatening reaction to medications or infections, characterized by extensive skin detachment and internal organ involvement.
treatment: Aggressive medical intervention in a specialized burn unit, including fluids, electrolytes, wound care, and immunosuppressant therapy.
prognosis: Ranging from complete recovery to severe skin damage and fatal complications.
